upporting telephony, student information, events, data collection, etc; Create and distribute analytics, reports, and dashboards for user departments; Provide change logs and documentation on updates made to the company\u2019s tech ecosystem including but not limited to: user audit trails, workflow processes, reporting, and analytics; Address user questions, aggregate and prioritize user feedback, and plan and implement system enhancements based on personal expertise, user feedback and organizational goals; Identify system problems, develop fixes, ensure full quality assurance testing, and implement solutions; Document and train staff on system best practices and processes; Research, review, recommend and implement new or replacement systems, features and updates to better support our ecosystem and company operations; and All other duties as assigned. Essential Knowledge, Skills and Abilities Very strong attention to detail; Excellent communication skills (verbal and written); Demonstrated success as a team player possessing a positive attitude, strong work ethic, entrepreneurial spirit, and flexibility; Systematic problem-solving skills, the ability to determine root cause problems and implement solutions; Able to handle multiple, complex priorities and balance the needs of each according to business impact; Proven ability to work in a fast-paced, high energy environment and juggle multiple deadlines and tasks; Exceptional project management skills including the ability to meet deadlines and handle diverse tasks simultaneously using prioritization; Successful implementation of business process documentation initiatives; Strong track record of acting with a customer-focused approach; and Proficient with technology especially cloud-based tools (eg. Google Apps,, Google Drive). Qualifications Two (2) years of experience working with a wide array of systems; One (1) year experience as a Salesforce Administrator; One (1) year experience with Asana or similar Project Management tool; Bachelor's degree or equivalent work experience; and Ability to pass required background check. Benefits Medical, dental, and vision employee coverage for as little as $1 each per month Personal paid time off in addition to major holidays Short-term disability insurance, long-term disability insurance, life insurance, and AD&D insurance all 100% paid by the employer 401(k) with employer contributing a dollar-for-dollar match of employee contributions up to 5% of employee earnings Best-in-class employee recognition platform, powered by Fond Employee discount program with instant access to pre-negotiated, best-rate-guaranteed discounts on hundreds of popular products and services from categories like fitness, travel, professional development, home services, entertainment and more. Job Type: Full-time Pay: $60,000.00 - $72,000.00 per year Benefits: 401(k) 401(k) Matching Dental Insurance Disability Insurance Health Insurance Life Insurance Paid Time Off Vision Insurance Experience: Salesforce Administrator: 1 year (Required) various systems: 2 years (Required) Asana or other Project Management tool: 1 year (Required) Application Question: Have you read and do you understand the salary range for this position? Work Location: One location Schedule: Monday to Friday Day shift Benefit Conditions: Waiting period may apply Only full-time employees eligible Work Remotely: Yes "
